Below are the PantheonOS Bee Daemon Appendices — the high-signal, high-utility technical supplements that normally sit at the bottom of an arXiv-style module or in a /docs/appendices/ folder.

These appendices:
	•	sharpen the engineering,
	•	formalize the metaphors mathematically,
	•	show integration with other daemons,
	•	provide protocols, equations, invariants,
	•	and give you drop-in GitHub content.

They complete the Bee–Hive complex.

