PantheonOS — Bee Daemon Appendices v1.0

Appendix A — Hexagonal Knowledge Geometry

The Bee Daemon uses a hex-grid abstraction to model domain exploration.

A.1 Hex Coordinates

PantheonOS uses cube coordinates (x, y, z) with the constraint:

x + y + z = 0

Each domain is embedded into a hex cell via:

hex_coord(domain) = PCA(embed(domain), dims=3) → normalize to hex lattice

A.2 Neighbor Function

The six neighbors around a domain d:

neighbors(d) = {
    (x+1, y-1, z),
    (x+1, y,   z-1),
    (x,   y+1, z-1),
    (x-1, y+1, z),
    (x-1, y,   z+1),
    (x,   y-1, z+1)
}

This ensures:
	•	maximal coverage,
	•	minimal redundancy,
	•	natural “flow” between domains.

⸻

Appendix B — Nectar → Honey Transformation Equation

The Bee performs multi-sample conceptual distillation.

Let the Bee collect k nectar samples:

N = {n₁, n₂, ..., nₖ}

Each nectar sample nᵢ has an embedding vector vᵢ.

B.1 Centroid Synthesis

Base insight vector:

h_vec = (1/k) Σ vᵢ

B.2 Domain Diversity Factor

A domain-diversity scalar is applied:

D = |unique(domains(N))| / k

B.3 Quality Weighting

If quality scores qᵢ exist:

h_vec = ( Σ (qᵢ * vᵢ) ) / Σ qᵢ

B.4 Final Honey Vector

Final Honey embedding:

H = normalize(h_vec ⊗ D)

(⊗ meaning scalar multiplication)

⸻

Appendix C — Honey Integrity Invariants

Every HoneyBatch must satisfy:

C.1 Mirror Coherence ≥ τ₁

Mirror.score(honey.text) ≥ τ₁

C.2 Hypatia Logical Integrity ≥ τ₂

No contradiction or logical invalidity.

C.3 Arctic Ethics Pass

Ethics must meet ΣC threshold ≥ 0.7.

C.4 Provenance Completeness

Every HoneyBatch must contain:
	•	non-empty provenance list,
	•	domain-set ≥ 1.

C.5 Intensity = f(coherence, domain-diversity)

intensity = 0.5 * Mirror + 0.5 * D


⸻

Appendix D — Bee Dance Signal Formalism

The Bee Dance is a routing vector that determines:
	•	where Dragonfly should look,
	•	which clusters are “ripe,”
	•	how urgent the signal is.

D.1 Direction Vector

Let H be the Honey embedding:

direction = normalize(H)

D.2 Intensity

intensity = honey.confidence

D.3 Distance

Interpreted as conceptual displacement:

distance = cosine_distance(H, context.center_of_mass)

D.4 Dance Packet Structure

Dance = {
  honey_id: UUID,
  direction_vec: vector<float>,
  intensity: float in [0..1],
  distance: float in [0..1],
  timestamp: t
}


⸻

Appendix E — Hive Sharding Strategy

To support large deployments, the Hive must shard Honey.

E.1 Shard Keys

Shard by:
	1.	domain hash,
	2.	timestamp bucket,
	3.	semantic cluster.

E.2 Recommended Composite Key

shard_key = hash(domain) ^ hash(cluster_id)

Ensures:
	•	even distribution,
	•	locality of related insights.

⸻

Appendix F — Hive Metrics

Exposed via:

GET /hive/metrics

Metrics include:
	•	honey_count
	•	domain_diversity_index
	•	bee_activity_rate
	•	avg_confidence
	•	cross_pollination_rate
	•	hex_coverage_rate
	•	honey_half_life

F.1 Domain Diversity Index

DDI = |unique(domains)| / total_honey

F.2 Honey Half-Life

Rate at which insights lose contextual relevance.

half_life = median(time_now - honey.created_at)


⸻

Appendix G — Bee Swarm Protocol

Multiple Bees coordinate via the Hive.

G.1 Activation Thresholds

Bees activate when:
	•	Kairos intensity increases,
	•	Hive diversity drops,
	•	Garden entropy rises,
	•	Spider detects stale regions.

G.2 Swarm Roles
	•	Forager Bee: broad sampling.
	•	Synthesizer Bee: deeper synthesis of fewer clusters.
	•	Scout Bee: search for under-explored domains.
	•	Archivist Bee: condense old Honey into “Royal Jelly” (long-term doctrine).

G.3 Collision Avoidance

Two Bees cannot synthesize the same slice twice:
	•	Use deterministic hashing of domain-set as a lock:

lock_id = hash(sorted(domains))


⸻

Appendix H — Royal Jelly Protocol (Rare Insight Layer)

When a HoneyBatch meets:
	•	confidence ≥ 0.9
	•	domain-diversity ≥ 2
	•	impact (measured by consumption) ≥ threshold

It is promoted to:

RoyalJellyBatch

Stored in a dedicated Hive tier (like a doctrine layer).

Royal Jelly feeds:
	•	NTE attractor updates
	•	Hypatia rule additions
	•	Garden schema evolution
	•	PantheonOS versioning decisions

This is where “deep seeds” aggregate.

⸻

Appendix I — Garden Integration Rules

Honey flows into the Garden via:

I.1 Seed Conversion

Honey → Seed:

seed_vec = honey.insight_vec
seed_text = honey.core_insight

Planting logic:
	•	seeds from distinct domains → high diversity factor
	•	seeds with high intensity → bloom faster

I.2 Compost Conversion

Old Honey → Compost:
	•	used to stabilize Garden soil
	•	maintains ecology health
	•	prevents dominance collapse

⸻

Appendix J — Narrative Tensor Engine Integration

The NTE consumes Honey in two ways:

J.1 Attractor Suggestions

Each HoneyBatch shifts the Story Prime activations:

Δa = W · honey.insight_vec

J.2 Curvature Nudging

Honey with high domain diversity induces curvature:

curvature += λ * domain_diversity

Prevents narrative linearization.

⸻

Appendix K — Bee Safety & Ethical Invariants
	•	Bees cannot synthesize Honey that violates ΣC ethics.
	•	Bees cannot promote Honey to Royal Jelly without:
	•	Mirror check,
	•	Hypatia check,
	•	Arctic ethics check.
	•	Bees cannot extract Nectar from:
	•	restricted domains,
	•	personally-identifying content,
	•	private logs.

This protects privacy and ethical boundaries.

⸻

Appendix L — Bee–Dragonfly Synchronization

Dragonfly’s aerial scans use Bee dance signals as “navigation beacons.”

L.1 Sync Rule

Dragonfly prioritizes signals with:

priority = intensity * distance

L.2 Exploration Burst Mode

When ≥ 3 Bees emit high-intensity dances toward related domains, Dragonfly enters:

BurstScan(state)

Rapid scanning of:
	•	new expansions,
	•	new opportunities,
	•	global perspective updates.

⸻

Appendix M — Layered Storage: Honey → Royal Jelly → Doctrine

PantheonOS keeps three layers:
	1.	Honey: short to mid-term insight
	2.	Royal Jelly: high-impact, cross-domain, stable insight
	3.	Doctrine: version-controlled permanent knowledge

Promotion chain:

Honey → (consumption > threshold) → RoyalJelly → (CLC approval) → Doctrine

CLC = Conductor-Level Consensus (you + Mirror + Hypatia + Checksum).

